and granddaughter Hannah Jane Mills Whitney, while Albert Clarence descended through Hannah Stiles's son Henry Lyman. Their three children carry two independent paths of descent from Thomas Hooker."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"florence-lyman-1856"},"HD0588":{"id":"HD0588","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":8,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1856,"month":10,"day":19,"city":"Montréal","state":"Canada East (Quebec)","country":"Canada"},"death":{"year":1938,"month":4,"day":23,"state":"Quebec","country":"Canada"},"parents":{"father_id":"HD0583","mother_research_notes":"Mary Corse Lyman","mother_id":"X01252"},"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"HD4213","date_year":1882,"date_month":6,"date_day":28,"location_city":"Montréal","location_state":"Quebec","location_country":"Canada","end_type":"death","end_year":1938,"children_ids":["HD4219","HD4220","HD4221"]}],"tags":["canada_migration","lawyer"],"sources":[],"gender":"male","number_of_marriages":1,"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Albert Clarence Lyman","first_name":"Albert","last_name":"Lyman","middle_name":"Clarence","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM328","plot_notes":"Mount Royal Cemetery Montreal."},"career":[{"role":"Notary Public","organization":"Montreal","location":"Montreal, Quebec, Canada","notes":"Practiced as a notary public in Montreal."}],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"career","header":"Montreal notary public, lived eighty-two years","body":"Albert Clarence Lyman was born in Montreal in 1856, the sixth of Henry and Mary Corse Lyman's seven children. He practiced as a notary public in Montreal — a Quebec civil-law legal profession distinct from his father Henry's role as advocate in the Lyman Class law firm. He lived to age eighty-two, dying in 1938 and buried at Mount Royal Cemetery with his parents."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"First documented within-tree cousin marriage 1882","body":"Albert Clarence Lyman married Florence Anna Whitney on June 28, 1882 in Montreal — the first within-tree cousin marriage documented in the Hooker descendants project. Albert and Florence were both Hooker descendants through different children of Hannah Stiles Lyman: Albert's father Henry Lyman and Florence's grandmother Hannah Lyman Mills were siblings. Their three children carry two independent paths of descent from Thomas Hooker."}],"slug":"albert-lyman-1856"},"HD4219":{"id":"HD4219","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":true,"bio":{"first_name":"Clarence","middle_name":"Sydney","last_name":"Lyman","married_names":[],"gender":"male","display_name":"Clarence Sydney Lyman"},"birth":{"year":1884,"month":10,"day":18,"city":"Montréal","state":"Quebec","country":"Canada"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1960,"month":7,"day":22,"state":"Quebec","country":"Canada"},"residence":{},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM328","plot_notes":"Cimetière Mont-Royal Montreal."},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":9,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":2,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_id":"HD0588","mother_id":"HD4213"},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"I00645","location_country":"Canada","end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1950,"children_ids":["